{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"0cb8af95-58b8-4330-ade3-e1bdca51329b","content":"No file found in the working directory — I'll provide the solution directly.\n\n## Converting to Compiled Bindings\n\nAdd `x:DataType` to your `ContentPage` to enable compiled bindings:\n\n```xml\n<ContentPage xmlns=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui\"\n             xmlns:x=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml\"\n             xmlns:vm=\"clr-namespace:YourApp.ViewModels\"\n             x:Class=\"YourApp.Views.SettingsPage\"\n             x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\">\n\n    <VerticalStackLayout Padding=\"20\" Spacing=\"15\">\n\n        <Label Text=\"{Binding Theme}\" FontSize=\"{Binding FontSize}\" />\n\n        <Switch IsToggled=\"{Binding NotificationsEnabled}\" />\n\n        <Slider Minimum=\"10\" Maximum=\"30\"\n                Value=\"{Binding FontSize}\" />\n\n    </VerticalStackLayout>\n</ContentPage>\n```\n\n## Catching Binding Errors at Build Time\n\nOnce `x:DataType` is set, the XAML compiler validates every `{Binding}` path against the declared type. A typo like `{Binding Thme}` becomes a **build error**, not a silent runtime failure.\n\nTo ensure this is active, confirm in your `.csproj`:\n\n```xml\n<!-- These are on by default in .NET MAUI but verify they aren't disabled -->\n<EnableXamlC>true</EnableXamlC>\n<MauiXamlCValidateBindings>true</MauiXamlCValidateBindings>\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n\n1. **`x:DataType`** — declares the compile-time type for all bindings in that scope.\n2. **Nested scopes** — use `x:DataType` on child elements (e.g., a `DataTemplate`) when the binding context changes.\n3. **Opt out locally** — use `x:DataType=\"\"` on a specific element if you need a dynamic binding escape hatch.\n4. Any mismatched property name or type now produces **error XC0045** at build time.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"6e933494-9042-4220-8220-cf6c4b313072","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The directory is empty and there's no file to work with. The user is asking about converting a hypothetical SettingsPage.xaml to use compiled bindings. I'll provide a concise answer with an example showing how to add `x:DataType` and catch binding errors at build time.","outputTokens":592,"requestId":"0820:6A01C:A15560:BA9FF8:69F2A778"},"id":"3572c2e6-542a-4742-ba20-d41415736f26","timestamp":"2026-04-30T00:51:18.443Z","parentId":"5b9aba16-e002-4bc9-b5e5-8209bfb52843"}
